kimononet.peer

Class Peer

  • java.lang.Object
    • kimononet.peer.Peer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable

    public class Peer
extends java.lang.Object
implements Parcelable
    The Peer object stores information about the peer that is unique to a specific peer. This information includes the peer's GPS location, velocity, human-readable name, and uniquely identifying peer address. A peer parcel contains the following fields: -id (PeerAddress/8) -location (GeoLocation/24) -velocity (GeoVelocity/12)
    Author:
    Zorayr Khalapyan
